{{Infobox diocese | jurisdiction = Diocese | name = Gegharkounik | latin = <!-- Latin name of the diocese (or archdiocese) --> | local = {{lang|hy|Գեղարքունիքի թեմ}} | image = Gavar Holy Mother of God church (3).jpg | image_size = | caption = Holy Mother of God Cathedral, [[Gavar]] <!---- Locations ----> | country = [[Armenia]] | territory = | province = <!-- Ecclesiastical province --> <!---- Statistics ----> | area_km2 = <!-- Area in square kilometers, automatically converted --> | area_sqmi = <!-- Area in square miles, automatically converted --> | area_footnotes = | population = ~235,000 | population_as_of = <small>2011</small> | churches = | congregations = <!-- Number of congregations in the diocese --> | schools = <!-- Number of church supported schools in the diocese --> | members = <!-- Number of members in the diocese --> <!---- Information ----> | denomination = [[Armenian Apostolic Church]] | rite = [[Armenian Rite]] | established = 1996 | cathedral = Holy Mother of God Cathedral, [[Gavar]] | cocathedral = | patron = <!-- Patron saint(s) of the diocese (or archdiocese) --> | patron_title = <!-- Use to override the default label "Patron saint" --> | priests = <!---- Current leadership ----> | patriarch = [[Karekin II]] | bishop = Bishop Markos Hovhannisyan | bishop_title = Primate <!---- Map ----> | map = | map_size = | map_caption = <!---- Website ----> | website = | footnotes = }}
'''Diocese of Gegharkounik''' ({{lang-hy|Գեղարքունիքի թեմ}} ''Gegharkuniki t'em''), is a diocese of the [[Armenian Apostolic Church]] covering the [[Gegharkunik Province]] of [[Armenia]]. The name is derived from the historic ''Gegharkunik canton'' of [[Syunik (historic province)]] province of ancient [[Kingdom of Armenia (antiquity)|Greater Armenia]].
The Diocese of Gegharkounik was officially founded on 30 May 1996, upon a [[kontakion]] issued by Catholicos [[Karekin I]]. The diocesan headquarters are located in the provincial capital [[Gavar]], with the seat being the Holy Mother of God Cathedral of the town.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.armenianchurch.org/index.jsp?sid=1&id=89&pid=19&lng=en|title=The Armenian Church - Mother See of Holy Etchmiadzin|publisher=}}</ref>
