A '''''mohra''''' is a [[necklace]] made of [[gold coin]]s worn by the bride at a [[Sikh]] [[wedding ceremony|wedding]]. The ''mohra'' is given to the groom by the bride's father, who places it around the bride's neck after the wedding ceremony.

