{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2014}}
'''Rufus Hollis Gause''' (July 1, 1925 – September 6, 2015), known as Dr. Hollis Gause,<ref name=WTJ group=1>{{cite journal|last=Land|first=Steven J.|title=TRIBUTE TO DR. R. HOLLIS GAUSE|journal=Wesleyan Theological Journal|date=April 1999|volume=34|series=1|pages=Pg. 261|url=http://wesley.nnu.edu/fileadmin/imported_site/wesleyjournal/1999-wtj-34-1.pdf|accessdate=5 April 2011}}</ref> was a leading [[Pentecostal]] theologian in the [[Church of God (Cleveland)]]. Gause began his teaching career in 1947 at [[Lee University|Lee College]] ([[Cleveland, Tennessee]]).  He became the first dean and director of the [[Church of God Theological Seminary|Church of God School of Theology]] in 1975.  Gause served as president of the ''Society for Pentecostal Studies'' from 1971 to 1972. Gause also Pastored The Warren Church of God in Warren, Michigan (Now known as The Maranatha Church of God) from 1982-1984.

Gause has authored books of both a popular and scholarly nature.<ref>{{cite web|last=Gause|first=R. Hollis|title=Barnes & Noble|url=http://productsearch.barnesandnoble.com/search/results.aspx?store=book&ATH=R.+Hollis+Gause|publisher=BN.com|accessdate=5 April 2011|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140510203845/http://productsearch.barnesandnoble.com/search/results.aspx?store=book&ATH=R.+Hollis+Gause|archivedate=10 May 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>  In 2006 he co-authored a book with [[Dr. Kimberly Ervin Alexander]] entitled ''Women in Leadership:  A Pentecostal Perspective'' published by the Church of God Theological Seminary's [[Center for Pentecostal Leadership and Care]].<ref>{{cite book |last1=Gause |first1=Hollis|title=Women In Leadership: A Pentecostal Perspective (Pentecostal Leadership Series) |year=2006 |location=Cleveland, TN |isbn=978-1-59684-170-3 |author2=Kimberly Alexander}}</ref> Gause died in 2015 at the age of 90.<ref>{{cite news|title=R. Hollis Gause|url=http://clevelandbanner.com/stories/r-hollis-gause,17324|accessdate=16 September 2015|agency=Cleveland Banner|date=8 September 2015}}</ref>

